%h1 Contest Categories

%p
  We will accept two types of entries for this contest:
  %br
  (1) Software applications that use data on Ghana to raise awareness or promote better decision-making. Applications can be for the web, mobile phones, or SMS and must address one of the 
  contest TOPICS.
  %br  (2) News articles that reflect excellence in data journalism. Articles must be between 1,500 and 2,500 words, include at least one visualization using data on Ghana and address one of 
  the contest TOPICS.

%h1 Contest Topics

%p
  Contestants must address one of the following topics in their entries:
  %br
  %strong (1) Health
  %br
  Any issue related to health in Ghana will be accepted. Topics could include, but are
  %em{:style => 'text-decoration: underline;'} not limited to:
  maternal or child health and mortality; nutrition; HIV and AIDS; non-communicable diseases; 
  mental health; reproductive health; and neglected diseases. 
  %br
  %strong (2) Education
  %br
  Any issue related to education in Ghana will be accepted. Topics could include, but are
  %em{:style => 'text-decoration: underline;'} not limited to:  
  student enrollment and attendance; teacher education at all levels; quality of education; 
  higher education; and vocational training.
  %br
  %strong (3) Environment
  %br
  Any issue related to the environment in Ghana will be accepted. Topics 
  could include, but are 
  %em{:style => 'text-decoration: underline;'} not limited to:
  climate change, flooding, sanitation, air quality, and noise pollution.  

%h1 Contest Data

%p
  Contestants must use
  %em{:style => 'text-decoration: underline;'} at least one dataset
  in their entries. Datasets must be publicly available and could include, but are
  %em{:style => 'text-decoration: underline;'}  not limited to:

  %ul{:style => 'font-size: 1.4em;'}
    %li Any datasets available through the (#{link_to 'Ghana Statistical Service', 'http://www.statsghana.gov.gh/'})
    %li The Demographic and Health Survey (#{link_to '(register with MEASURE DHS)', 'http://www.measuredhs.com/countries/country_main.cfm?ctry_id=14'})
    %li 2000 Ghana Census (#{link_to '(register with IPUMS)', 'https://international.ipums.org/international-action/users/login'})
   
